    "summary": "I am a dramaturg and researcher specialising in the intersection of art, humanities and technology. My interests and expertise have led me to collaborate internationally with various cultural organisations such as IMPAKT.NL - Centre for Media Culture, FIBER Festival, Goethe-Institut e.V., Dimitria Festival, and Duncan Dance Research Centre. Through these collaborations, I have curated, produced, or coordinated a diverse range of projects and events that foster and showcase creative practices.\n\nMy focus lies in exploring the profound impact of technology on cultural expression within local and global communities. With a keen interest in the intersection of art, humanities, and technology, my research and practice delve into how technological advancements shape and influence artistic practices, cultural experiences, and societal dynamics.\n\nAt the moment, I am the Programme Coordinator of Immersive Tech Week, supporting the curation of the programme, which brings together artists, technologists, and tech enthusiasts to delve into the possibilities and implications of immersive technologies.",
