                    "day": null,
                    "year": 2015
                }
            },
            "description": "\"MALALA\", is a multimedia performance that took place in Aristotle University of Thessaloniki, during June 2015.  Based on Malala Yousafzai' s real story, the initial aim of this project was to investigate how a real story can be represented through multiple media such as books, theatre, tv shows or even pop songs, questioning how multimedia representation can affect or furthermore distort reality itself. \n\nConception, Directing: Anastasia Barka\nLight Design: Eleni Tsona\nVideo Capture: Greg Babalas\nPerformers: Ellie Chroniari, Savvina Georgiou, Chrysoula Flampoutoglou\n*The dramaturgy of the project was structured through a collective creative process",
