                    "company": "| | | space- Duncan Dance Research Center",
                    "description": "The scope of the work is to re-imagine human-nature relations and create \"a caring for the earth | caring for each other\" spatial narrative. Using an eco-choreographic approach, in this peripatetic route the participants are invited to form and construct their dramaturgical interpretations.\nThey walk through spaces that brace mobility and place the body in. They meet the performative language of poetry that stimulates engagement with the landscape. The project views the city as a collection of scenographic settings. Treating buildings, roads, pocket parks, and squares, as frames, it theatricalizes the real space and challenges the common perception of the city. The third space is an invitation towards rethinking how we gather and the practices that we share when we do.",
